strategy: Create three separate CTEs for store, catalog, and web sales, each aggregating both years (1999, 2000) in a single pass with conditional aggregation. Then join these three CTEs on customer_id (1 join
what_worked: Applied single_pass_aggregation, early_filter, dimension_cte_isolate, pushdown achieving 1.61x speedup
why_it_worked: Consolidating repeated scans into CASE aggregates reduces I/O from N scans to 1; Applying selective filters early reduces intermediate row counts before expensive operations; Pre-filtering all dimension tables into CTEs avoids repeated full-table scans; Pushing predicates closer to table scans reduces data volume in upper operators
